{"questionId":"13690961","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Mosaic Industries negotiates a new deal with their phone case supplier. Under the new deal, the supplier agrees to discount the cost of each case based on the number of cases purchased by Mosaic Industries. The cost charged by the supplier for each case can be found using the function</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>C</mi><mfenced><mi>n</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>10</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0001</mn><mi>n</mi></math></p>\n<p>where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>n</mi></math> represents the number of cases sold by Mosaic Industries.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence, write down the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced></math> that can be used to predict Mosaic Industries’ average monthly income, before expenses, at any selling price, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> .</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>x</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>1000</mn><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR</strong>&nbsp; &nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>R</mi><mfenced><mi>x</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mn>20</mn><mo> </mo><mn>000</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>1000</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[1 mark]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13690961","referenceCode":"23N.2.SL.TZ1.5c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence, write down the function R x that can be used to predict Mosaic Industries’ average monthly income, before expenses, at any selling price, x .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.5—Modelling functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.6—Modelling skills"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
